If Harmony makes 50 note pads (5 letter size pieces of paper folded three times = 125 sheets, and 125 sheets stapled together = 25 notepads), and each notepad has 10 notes, then one notepad would last for 10 days.

However, this assumes that the person writing the notes does not run out of paper before the end of the day. If they do, then the notepad will not last as long as expected. Additionally, if the person writes more than 10 notes per day, then the notepad will not last as long either.

In conclusion, while one notepad may last for 10 days under ideal conditions, it is important to consider how much paper is actually being used and how many notes are being written each day in order to determine the actual lifespan of the notepad.
